13. in Pauli pugna: if this means the battle at Pydna. and we know of no other which can be meant, the punishment of the centurion was postponed for 26 years: for Paulus defeated Perseus at Pydna in 168, and Scipio was censor in 142. It must be remembered that Scipio had fought under his father at Pydna (Liv. xliv. 44). and had probably himself wit- nessed or heard at the time of the cow- ardice of this centurion. Aemilius Paulus was himself censor in nc. 164.
